OK.  I think I got this one figured.  The copper 'arm' that rides the
rheostat had managed to get itself tweaked, after all of the times I had
been pulling the whole business apart.  I massaged & coaxed the 'arm' back
to a resonably straight form, and the dimmer seems to be behaving itself.

